00:48:33.278 --> 00:48:35.913
[overlapping chatter]

976
00:48:46.257 --> 00:48:48.393
[Grown Kanan] <i>Every hood
got a cop like Malcolm Howard.</i>

977
00:48:48.426 --> 00:48:50.428
<i>Act like he own the streets.</i>

978
00:48:50.461 --> 00:48:52.630
<i>Like we all answer to his ass.</i>

979
00:48:52.664 --> 00:48:55.600
<i>Like he the biggest gangster
around the way.</i>

980
00:48:55.633 --> 00:48:58.269
<i>But it ain't that simple.</i>

981
00:48:58.303 --> 00:49:00.271
<i>It ain't never that simple.</i>

982
00:49:01.406 --> 00:49:03.408
Looks like baby boy's
balls dropped.

983
00:49:07.345 --> 00:49:09.047
The block's the same.
him and his boys.

984
00:49:09.080 --> 00:49:10.548
they got prices on their heads.

985
00:49:10.581 --> 00:49:12.283
Yeah. well...

986
00:49:12.317 --> 00:49:14.319
block's got it wrong.

987
00:49:14.352 --> 00:49:18.323
Maybe you should. uh.
get out while you still can.

988
00:49:26.964 --> 00:49:28.566
They hit the wrong house.

989
00:49:28.599 --> 00:49:30.301
Just a fucked up mistake.

990
00:49:30.335 --> 00:49:33.137
Hmm. That's your story.
You're stickin' to it?

991
00:49:33.171 --> 00:49:34.372
That's the one.

992
00:49:36.207 --> 00:49:37.408
You spinnin' that same shit?

993
00:49:37.442 --> 00:49:40.011
My son don't got nothing
to say to you.

994
00:49:43.614 --> 00:49:45.583
Watch your back. Raquel.

995
00:49:47.485 --> 00:49:49.687
And keep them eyes open. B.

996
00:49:57.261 --> 00:49:58.730
[Marvin] Yo. let us through.
man. we family.

997
00:49:58.763 --> 00:50:00.732
Yo. Raq.

998
00:50:00.765 --> 00:50:02.433
[Marvin] You a'ight?

999
00:50:02.467 --> 00:50:04.736
Guns wasn't pointed
in the air this time.

1000
00:50:07.004 --> 00:50:08.740
It's your first crime scene.
Burke.

1001
00:50:08.773 --> 00:50:10.608
What do you got?

1002
00:50:10.641 --> 00:50:13.010
[sighs]
Nine-millimeter shell casings.

1003
00:50:13.044 --> 00:50:14.245
Some sort of SMG.

1004
00:50:14.278 --> 00:50:16.314
Gonna run ballistics.
see if we can match it.

1005
00:50:16.347 --> 00:50:18.716
Ah. you all sleuthing up
in this motherfucker. huh?

1006
00:50:18.750 --> 00:50:20.651
Just doin' my job.

1007
00:50:20.685 --> 00:50:22.453
[Howard] Yeah. well.
I hope you're a good swimmer.

1008
00:50:22.487 --> 00:50:24.255
The gat that
squeezed that shit out

1009
00:50:24.288 --> 00:50:26.290
it's already at the bottom
of Baisley Pond.

1010
00:50:31.729 --> 00:50:33.464
[Jukebox] Shit's scary. right?

1011
00:50:33.498 --> 00:50:38.069
Psh. Shit's so scary. I didn't
even have time to be scared.

1012
00:50:39.504 --> 00:50:42.140
[police radio chatter]

1013
00:50:43.508 --> 00:50:45.176
I'm glad they missed.

1014
00:50:46.644 --> 00:50:48.246
Yeah. me too.

1015
00:50:52.283 --> 00:50:53.351
Yo.

1016
00:50:55.653 --> 00:50:57.188
Where was you at earlier?

1017
00:51:00.191 --> 00:51:01.592
White girl?

1018
00:51:08.366 --> 00:51:11.302
You know I'd never tell you
how to raise your son. Raq.

1019
00:51:11.335 --> 00:51:12.603
[tense music]

1020
00:51:12.637 --> 00:51:15.139
But them fools
is comin' for Kanan.

1021
00:51:15.173 --> 00:51:18.843
And no escalator in no school
is gonna save him from that.

1022
00:51:19.076 --> 00:51:20.711
Neither is his mama.

1023
00:51:20.745 --> 00:51:23.748
♪ ♪

1024
00:51:31.322 --> 00:51:32.457
[Raq] <i>For Buck's family.</i>

1025
00:51:37.094 --> 00:51:38.596
Sss.

1026
00:51:38.629 --> 00:51:41.232
We had a truce. Raq.

1027
00:51:41.265 --> 00:51:43.501
that your boy
and his crew violated.

1028
00:51:43.534 --> 00:51:46.204
Now. you think a grip of cash
for Buck's family

1029
00:51:46.237 --> 00:51:48.306
gonna nearly fix that. Raq?

1030
00:51:48.339 --> 00:51:50.808
If our word don't count.
this whole shit falls apart.

1031
00:51:50.842 --> 00:51:52.210
You know that.

1032
00:51:52.243 --> 00:51:53.444
Speakin' on violations.

1033
00:51:53.478 --> 00:51:55.546
You came after my son
last night--

1034
00:51:55.580 --> 00:51:56.581
where we stay at.

1035
00:51:56.614 --> 00:51:58.683
And we gonna keep comin'. Raq.

1036
00:51:58.716 --> 00:52:00.651
You see. I got money
on all them niggas' heads

1037
00:52:00.685 --> 00:52:03.254
until you and I
come to an agreement.

1038
00:52:03.287 --> 00:52:05.590
Or until we don't need to
no more.

1039
00:52:05.623 --> 00:52:06.824
Now. look.

1040
00:52:06.858 --> 00:52:09.260
I want all them corners.

1041
00:52:09.293 --> 00:52:12.263
No compromise. no split.

1042
00:52:12.296 --> 00:52:13.564
no nothing.

1043
00:52:13.598 --> 00:52:15.833
They all comin' to me now.

1044
00:52:15.867 --> 00:52:18.302
See. look.

1045
00:52:18.336 --> 00:52:20.705
My crew's lookin' at me like...

1046
00:52:20.738 --> 00:52:24.809
if I don't bring somethin' back
real for Buck.

1047
00:52:24.842 --> 00:52:27.411
they gonna start
wantin' answers to questions

1048
00:52:27.445 --> 00:52:30.648
people in our position
don't ever wanna be asked. Raq.

1049
00:52:30.681 --> 00:52:32.617
Kanan's not to be touched.

1050
00:52:32.650 --> 00:52:34.485
I'll dead the bounty.

1051
00:52:34.519 --> 00:52:35.853
But you gotta understand this:

1052
00:52:35.887 --> 00:52:39.190
I can only control
what I can control.

1053
00:52:39.223 --> 00:52:41.893
See. Buck's got a lot of people
on the Southside. Raq.

1054
00:52:43.661 --> 00:52:45.863
And I can't be held responsible

1055
00:52:45.897 --> 00:52:48.266
for random niggas wantin'
to take matters

1056
00:52:48.299 --> 00:52:49.467
into they own hands.

1057
00:52:49.500 --> 00:52:50.768
Kanan's not in this.

1058
00:52:50.801 --> 00:52:53.604
Kanan's you and Def Con's boy.
Raq.

1059
00:52:53.638 --> 00:52:54.906
That nigga been in this shit

1060
00:52:54.939 --> 00:52:58.175
before he was even
in this shit.

1061
00:52:58.209 --> 00:52:59.877
That's why I always say
this hustle right here

1062
00:52:59.911 --> 00:53:02.446
ain't for the broads. Raq.
[chuckles]

1063
00:53:02.480 --> 00:53:04.482
'Cause you see. in this shit.

1064
00:53:04.515 --> 00:53:07.718
you can't give a fuck
about nobody or nothing

1065
00:53:07.752 --> 00:53:09.720
more than your business.

1066
00:53:09.754 --> 00:53:13.925
Distractions make you weak.
Make you blink.

1067
00:53:13.958 --> 00:53:15.359
You don't care about your son

1068
00:53:15.393 --> 00:53:17.361
any less
than I care about Kanan.

1069
00:53:18.596 --> 00:53:19.664
Listen.

1070
00:53:22.333 --> 00:53:23.968
Jerome's my heart.

1071
00:53:24.201 --> 00:53:26.837
but he ain't live inside of me.

1072
00:53:26.871 --> 00:53:28.873
He didn't come out of me. Raq.

1073
00:53:28.906 --> 00:53:31.442
You see. you and Kanan
connected in a way

1074
00:53:31.475 --> 00:53:34.679
me and Jerome
just never will be. Raq.

1075
00:53:34.712 --> 00:53:36.881
You can't fuck
with that chemistry.

1076
00:53:36.914 --> 00:53:38.349
It's biology.

1077
00:53:38.382 --> 00:53:42.520
[chuckles]
Even worse. Raq.

1078
00:53:42.553 --> 00:53:43.654
Listen.

1079
00:53:43.688 --> 00:53:46.357
[tense music playing]

1080
00:53:46.390 --> 00:53:48.392
All them corners is mine now.

1081
00:53:48.426 --> 00:53:51.295
♪ ♪

1082
00:53:57.935 --> 00:54:00.004
I'm not blinkin'. 'Nique.

1083
00:54:00.237 --> 00:54:01.939
My eyes are wide fuckin' open.

1084
00:54:21.959 --> 00:54:24.929
[foreboding music playing]

1085
00:54:24.962 --> 00:54:27.365
♪ ♪

1086
00:54:27.398 --> 00:54:28.566
[Raq] Kanan.

1087
00:54:31.369 --> 00:54:32.903
[whispering]
Get dressed. We're goin'.

1088
00:54:32.937 --> 00:54:34.472
Goin' where?

1089
00:54:34.505 --> 00:54:35.873
Just get dressed.

1090
00:55:33.464 --> 00:55:35.566
Thought you were takin' me
to Grandma's.

1091
00:55:38.903 --> 00:55:40.404
How'd that test go?

1092
00:55:41.806 --> 00:55:44.008
For real.

1093
00:55:44.041 --> 00:55:45.776
Don't lie to me.

1094
00:55:48.446 --> 00:55:51.415
If there was a lot of answers
in that B column.

1095
00:55:51.449 --> 00:55:52.683
I might be a'ight.

1096
00:55:54.852 --> 00:55:56.921
[exhales]
You threw it.

1097
00:55:59.490 --> 00:56:02.093
Kanan went hard on them Bs.

1098
00:56:14.371 --> 00:56:17.007
You see those four stars?
Right there.

1099
00:56:17.041 --> 00:56:19.610
That rectangle.

1100
00:56:19.643 --> 00:56:22.413
With those diagonal stars
right in the middle of them.

1101
00:56:23.981 --> 00:56:25.883
That's Orion the Hunter.

1102
00:56:28.886 --> 00:56:30.654
That's us. Kanan.

1103
00:56:31.756 --> 00:56:33.457
Orion.

1104
00:56:33.491 --> 00:56:35.793
Always the hunter.
never the hunted.

1105
00:56:53.811 --> 00:56:55.579
Go ahead. Take it.

1106
00:56:58.048 --> 00:56:59.416
Point it straight out there.

1107
00:56:59.450 --> 00:57:00.417
[ominous music playing]

1108
00:57:00.451 --> 00:57:02.586
Hold that shit with two hands.

1109
00:57:02.620 --> 00:57:04.722
Strong hand on top.

1110
00:57:06.924 --> 00:57:08.559
Extend your arms.

1111
00:57:08.592 --> 00:57:10.961
Aim straight out there.

1112
00:57:11.896 --> 00:57:13.697
Squeeze one off.

1113
00:57:21.739 --> 00:57:24.074
That bullet's out there now.

1114
00:57:24.108 --> 00:57:27.912
Circlin' the world
with your name on it.

1115
00:57:27.945 --> 00:57:30.447
And you gonna be runnin'
from it for forever.

1116
00:57:32.183 --> 00:57:34.718
You wanted to be in it?

1117
00:57:34.752 --> 00:57:36.720
You in it.

1118
00:57:36.754 --> 00:57:39.757
♪ ♪

1119
00:57:56.774 --> 00:57:59.743
[punchy percussive music]

1120
00:57:59.777 --> 00:58:02.746
♪ ♪

1121
00:58:02.780 --> 00:58:04.715
[gunshot]

1122
00:58:20.998 --> 00:58:23.067
[Grown Kanan] <i>You already know
how my shit ended.</i>

1123
00:58:25.803 --> 00:58:27.137
<i>And now you know
how it started.</i>

1124
00:58:27.171 --> 00:58:28.873
[gunshot]

1125
00:58:29.874 --> 00:58:32.776
<i>But the real story
is what happened in between.</i>

1126
00:58:34.945 --> 00:58:36.580
<i>This is that story.</i>

1127
00:58:38.282 --> 00:58:39.750
<i>This is my story.</i>

1128
00:58:41.085 --> 00:58:43.921
<i>This is a Southside. Jamaica.
Queens story.</i>

1129
00:58:47.892 --> 00:58:49.126
[Main Source's
"Just Hangin' Out"]

1130
00:58:49.159 --> 00:58:51.829
[singer]
<i>♪ I'm just hangin' out ♪</i>

1131
00:58:51.862 --> 00:58:53.664
<i>♪ I'm mainly known
For the rough raps ♪</i>

1132
00:58:53.697 --> 00:58:55.799
<i>♪ But kids steal my lyrics
Like hubcaps ♪</i>

1133
00:58:55.833 --> 00:58:58.636
<i>♪ And eat 'em like stacks of
Flapjacks like Rugrats ♪</i>

1134
00:58:58.669 --> 00:59:01.171
<i>♪ Hey. and I get busy
Over unknown tracks ♪</i>

1135
00:59:01.205 --> 00:59:04.174
<i>♪ While the next man flaps
His lids like Parkay ♪</i>

1136
00:59:04.208 --> 00:59:07.077
<i>♪ I'm skilled in the field.
So slide to the side ♪</i>

1137
00:59:07.111 --> 00:59:08.579
<i>♪ I'll make a rapper cry ♪</i>

1138
00:59:08.612 --> 00:59:10.247
<i>♪ 'Cause I can get
Some shut-eye ♪</i>

1139
00:59:10.281 --> 00:59:12.650
<i>♪ While he's havin'
Hard times writin' rhymes ♪</i>

1140
00:59:12.683 --> 00:59:15.986
<i>♪ So he gnaws on my metaphors
And dines on my lines ♪</i>

1141
00:59:16.020 --> 00:59:18.188
<i>♪ Which is the reason why
I like to hang out ♪</i>

1142
00:59:18.222 --> 00:59:21.225
<i>♪ And hustle with my friends
To get away from pens ♪</i>

1143
00:59:21.258 --> 00:59:23.894
<i>♪ And copiers
So I'm Corona bound ♪</i>

1144
00:59:23.928 --> 00:59:26.196
<i>♪ To check Drew
AKA Doc the Butcher ♪</i>

1145
00:59:26.230 --> 00:59:27.598
<i>♪ And what's goin' down ♪</i>

1146
00:59:27.631 --> 00:59:29.233
<i>♪ And Joe with the Jetta ♪</i>

1147
00:59:29.266 --> 00:59:31.602
<i>♪ Enables us
To get around town ♪</i>

1148
00:59:31.635 --> 00:59:32.970
<i>♪ He's a clown ♪</i>

1149
00:59:33.003 --> 00:59:35.572
<i>♪ Other than that.
I'm with Joe Burgos ♪</i>

1150
00:59:35.606 --> 00:59:37.908
<i>♪ Watch an old Black Caesar
Flick for kicks ♪</i>

1151
00:59:37.942 --> 00:59:39.743
<i>♪ Jump in the wagon
And we're outta here ♪</i>

1152
00:59:39.777 --> 00:59:41.779
<i>♪ Without an idea of where ♪</i>

1153
00:59:41.812 --> 00:59:44.081
<i>♪ But usually
We wind up there ♪</i>

1154
00:59:44.114 --> 00:59:46.250
<i>♪ I go over K-Cut's block ♪</i>

1155
00:59:46.283 --> 00:59:49.286
<i>♪ 'Cause rock cuts
Is what he blends ♪</i>

1156
00:59:49.320 --> 00:59:52.289
[singer vocalizing]

1157
00:59:52.323 --> 00:59:55.092
♪ ♪

1158
00:59:55.125 --> 00:59:57.962
[laughter]
